        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 13 at 4:01PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 401 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms along a line extending from near Millport to near
Ethelsville. Movement was southeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Aliceville, Reform, Carrollton, Pickensville, Ethelsville, McMullen,
Garden, Johnston Lake, Dillburg, North Pickens Airport, McShan, Shaw,
George Downer Airport, Owens, and Macedonia.
</description>
        <instruction>Torrential rainfall is also occurring with these storms and may lead
to localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
